cs.NI, cs.HC, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA 

The paper discusses the use of wireless communication and sensor nodes for healthcare monitoring, which falls under the category of networked systems and internet of things. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on healthcare applications, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The discussion of different standards and devices used in WBANs suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the impact of path loss on communication, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
